.\" termin.al-name: pwd
.\" termin.al-usage: pwd
.\" termin.al-summary: Print this shell pane's virtual directory.
.TH PWD 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
pwd \- Print this shell pane's virtual directory.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
pwd
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints the canonical virtual working directory owned by the current shell pane. Virtual home is written as
.B ~
and descendants as paths such as
.BR ~/notes .
.SH OUTPUT
Exactly one text output is added to the current pane transcript.
.SH FAILURES
Any argument is rejected.
.SH NOTES
Each shell pane owns its directory independently. The value survives clear(1) and pane-tree transforms while the pane exists, but is not browser-persisted across reloads.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ pwd
$ cd notes
$ pwd
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
cd(1), ls(1), pane(1)
